AIAppTaggingProtocol Protocol Reference

Conforms to NSObject
Declared in AIAppTaggingProtocol.h

Overview

A protocol declaring methods to tag application events like action and navigation

– createInstanceForComponent:componentVersion: required method

This method creates and returns a tagging wrapper object which can be used for tracking actions and navigation.

- (nonnull id<AIAppTaggingProtocol>)createInstanceForComponent:(nonnull NSString *)componentId componentVersion:(nonnull NSString *)componentVersion

Parameters

componentId

Identifier of the requesting component
componentVersion

Version of the requesting component

Return Value

Returns an object that conforms to ‘AITaggingProtocol’ protocol.

– trackTimedActionStart:data: required method

Tracks the start of a timed event

- (void)trackTimedActionStart:(nullable NSString *)action data:(nullable NSDictionary *)data

Parameters

action

a required NSString value that denotes the action name to track.
data

optional dictionary pointer containing context data to track with this timed action.

Discussion

Note: This method does not send a tracking hit @attention If an action with the same name already exists it will be deleted and a new one will replace it.

Declared In

AIAppTaggingProtocol.h

– trackTimedActionEnd:logic: required method

Tracks the end of a timed event

- (void)trackTimedActionEnd:(nullable NSString *)action logic:(nullable BOOL ( ^ ) ( NSTimeInterval inAppDuration , NSTimeInterval totalDuration , NSMutableDictionary *__nullable data ))block

Parameters

action

a required NSString pointer that denotes the action name to finish tracking.
block

optional block to perform logic and update parameters when this timed event ends, this block can cancel the sending of the hit by returning NO.

Discussion

Note: This method will send a tracking hit if the parameter logic is nil or returns YES.
